metadata.name: Penumbra #234
metadata.description:
Penumbra is a geometric exploration of the possible outcomes from 3 basic rules:

1) Place some walls
2) Place some light sources
3) Draw the resulting shadows

This series is a small thank you to the collectors of Umbra :)

metadata.name: a reveure! #61
metadata.description:
a reveure! is a catalan farewell expression. this collection is a souvenir to celebrate me meeting up with artists, collectors and friends during 2023s summer art events (Responsive Dreams in Barcelona and NFT Show Europe in Valencia). 
mechanics to get a piece: say hi and chat with me to get a free pass to mint your iteration and its signed miniprint. ill be doing mobile live minting on small screen (iPad/phone) during Barcelona and Valencia events. 

a reveure! is about simplifying my painting brushes style used in previous works, in an attempt to find minimalist and more conceptual approach. using only black and white and minimizing the use of random, i explore the void and the spaces generated on the canvas, discovering how abstract sculpture-like figures emerge. raw edges and big brushes make the eye confused as it seems 3D shapes building up. 

this line of work and the concept behind it was inspired by Elena Asins computer art from late XXs century.

the motion restarts every 20sec
press [s] or click/touch to save an image
press [r] to reload 
press [1] - [9] to make higher resolution
press [c] to make brushes spin
press left/right arrows to move brushes left/right

made with love and p5js

thank you fxhash team to give me the opportunity and tools to do this special mobile live minting

Marc L Clapers / mekhno
summer 2023

metadata.name: Wires #78
metadata.description:
Cut, pulled, twisted wires.
Some reach their destination, others will never arrive.
Wires forming weaves and figures, sometimes linear, sometimes chaotic but, in their simplicity they create harmonious intertwining.

Press "p" to pause, press again "p" to start again.
Press "s" to save as jpg.

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Galactica #94
metadata.description:
Galactica shows us the landscapes of a distant exoplanetary system made up of 10 planets.
Standing on one of these planets with its particular geomorphology, we may see faraway galaxies, natural satellites and/or another planet in the sky.

The combination of the various features can give life to up to 415,000 different versions, taking into account the differences not related to features the versions rise to about 12 billion.

Press "s" to get a 2000x2000 pixels jpg.

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: GLYPH #47
metadata.description:
creator: 404src
date: 2022-03-19
twitter: @404src
platform: Pico-8, Lua

GLYPH is a collection of patterned waveforms with varying
forms and volatility. Best enjoyed after meeting a hard deadline.

10% of GLYPHs are unstable, causing their frame to move
and distort.
